mention.text: Iraq 's Saddam , with whom the king met Monday sought to `` turn the gulf into a lake of peace free of foreign fleets and forces that harbor ill intentions against us
Iranian territory and release soldiers captured during the Iran-Iraq war

Washington seeking to mediate the Persian Gulf crisis President Bush on Tuesday said the United States may extend the United States naval quarantine to Jordan 's Red Sea port of Aqaba to shut off Iraq 's last unhindered trade route In another mediation effort , the Soviet Union said today another mediation effort had sent an envoy to the Middle East on a series of stops to include Baghdad Soviet officials also said Soviet women , children and invalids would be allowed to leave Iraq President Bush today denounced Saddam 's `` ruinous policies of war , '' and said the United States is `` striking a blow for the principle that might does not make right
Iran , read by a broadcaster over Baghdad radio
Iran , which had condemned Iraq 's invasion of Kuwait on Aug. 2
